    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>The year is 431, and [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' invasion has shattered all major opposition in the Tiers. The [url=glossary:younger realms]Younger Realms[/url], the Bastard Tier, the Free Cities - all who defied [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] lay broken by battle or bowed in surrender.

The two armies of the Overlord - the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] and the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] - now control our lands.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>But our will is not yet extinguished, not entirely. In the valley of [url=glossary:vendrien's well]Vendrien's Well[/url], those of us unwilling to bow to [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] have banded together in defiance.

Violating an oath of surrender from two years prior, we have staged a bloody uprising - murdering the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] and [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] garrison in a midnight assault.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>With their main forces spread across the Tiers, the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] and [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] redeploy to [url=glossary:vendrien's well]Vendrien's Well[/url] to crush the resistance, but months pass with no definitive battle.

As disagreement and discord paralyze the Archons, we bide our time and wait for our message of insurrection to spread across the Tiers.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Overlord is not amused, and [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] has one message for the Archons: crush the oathbreakers or die. [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] backs this threat with an [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url], a magical commandment that can slay all in the valley should the order be ignored.

The honor of proclaiming this [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] fell to you. Sent across the mountains to [url=glossary:vendrien's well]Vendrien's Well[/url], you carry the Overlord's [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] to read before the Archons.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
